## Dipole Antenna Design at 10.9 GHz

## 1. Project Overview

This project involves the design and electromagnetic simulation of a **half-wave dipole antenna** using **ANSYS High Frequency Structure Simulator (HFSS)**.

The antenna is designed to operate at **10.9 GHz** and is analyzed through electromagnetic simulation to evaluate its RF performance characteristics, including impedance matching, return loss, gain, directivity, radiation pattern, and efficiency.

The project demonstrates the fundamental behavior of a dipole antenna and its application in wireless communication and RF systems.

## 2. Software and Tools

**Simulation Software:**

* ANSYS High Frequency Structure Simulator (HFSS)

**Analysis Tools:**

* MATLAB (optional for post-processing)

